00:00:01.100 --> 00:00:02.460
JOHN DOLHUN: You got the sock?

00:00:02.460 --> 00:00:03.960
OK.

00:00:03.960 --> 00:00:07.660
So I'm just going to put
the sock in here.

00:00:07.660 --> 00:00:08.770
He's going to catch it.

00:00:08.770 --> 00:00:11.400
[LOUD POPPING NOISE]

00:00:11.400 --> 00:00:13.440
There it goes.

00:00:13.440 --> 00:00:15.200
Let's check his sock out.

00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:17.308
Is it still OK?

00:00:17.308 --> 00:00:55.290
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:55.290 --> 00:00:57.260
NARRATOR: It's day one.

00:00:57.260 --> 00:01:00.440
MIT instructor John Dolhun
introduces the course.

00:01:00.440 --> 00:01:03.640
JOHN DOLHUN: You're going to
learn basic skills that will

00:01:03.640 --> 00:01:08.350
form building blocks in your
future adventures at MIT and

00:01:08.350 --> 00:01:09.890
outside of MIT.

00:01:09.890 --> 00:01:13.250
NARRATOR: That is,
if you pass.

00:01:13.250 --> 00:01:15.220
And what exactly
does that take?

00:01:15.220 --> 00:01:18.500
JOHN DOLHUN: You're going to get
about 14 hours of lecture,

00:01:18.500 --> 00:01:21.630
about 52 to 75 hours of lab.

00:01:21.630 --> 00:01:25.460
We only have two and
a half weeks.

00:01:25.460 --> 00:01:30.230
You have to be able to think out
of the box, be creative,

00:01:30.230 --> 00:01:34.720
and most importantly, be mindful
of your mistakes.

00:01:34.720 --> 00:01:36.090
PHIL: The hoods are
over there...

00:01:36.090 --> 00:01:38.290
NARRATOR: Next, safety
training.

00:01:38.290 --> 00:01:41.030
Remember, for many of the
students this is their first

00:01:41.030 --> 00:01:42.200
time in the lab.

00:01:42.200 --> 00:01:46.610
No flip-flops, no shorts, no
skirts, but most importantly,

00:01:46.610 --> 00:01:48.760
gloves and goggles starting
tomorrow.

00:01:48.760 --> 00:01:51.190
PHIL: They tell you to wear
goggles and everything.

00:01:51.190 --> 00:01:53.460
And you don't really realize the
importance until you have

00:01:53.460 --> 00:01:55.830
a piece of glass flying
at your face.

00:01:55.830 --> 00:01:58.690
NARRATOR: After four hours of
lecture, the students finally

00:01:58.690 --> 00:01:59.780
check into the lab.

